        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">This memorandum is probably the page of notes referred to in the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1071.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, [14 March 1847]</ref>. It is likely that the two men did not meet in London on 4 March as they had planned (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1068.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to J. D. Hooker, [1 March 1847]</ref>, n. 2), and that Hooker forwarded his notes on CD’s essay of 1844 on or shortly after the date of the proposed meeting.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><hi rend="italic">Epacridaceae</hi>, a family of shrubs mainly found in New Holland (Australia).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">In addition to these notes, Hooker made annotations on the fair copy of CD’s essay (DAR 113).</note>
